    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Who am I?</h2>
      <p>I have been living in Sofia, Bulgaria for a few years now, and I have been passionate about history since I was a child. From the World War I battlefields in Alsace to the World War II bunkers in the south of France, and now to the abandoned Cold War bases here in Bulgaria — history has always been how I spend my free time.</p>
      <p>A big fan of flea markets, I started collecting historical objects at the age of 12. Since moving to Sofia, I decided to dedicate all my free time to the subject of the People's Republic of Bulgaria.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Why this website?</h2>
      <p>After noticing a lack of information and a kind of "taboo" around the People's Republic of Bulgaria here in Bulgaria, I decided in 2023 to create an Instagram page dedicated to my collection: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/peoplesrepublicofbulgaria/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram Page</a>. This way, people from all over the world could learn more about this short historical period (1944–1990).</p>
      <p>Then in 2024, as a full-time enthusiast, I built this website to bring together the history of the People's Republic of Bulgaria, my collection, tourist sites to visit, and souvenirs to buy — all in one place. So anyone interested in this topic doesn't need to search through 10 different websites to find what they're looking for.</p>
      <p>History can of course be controversial. In creating this site, I tried to be as neutral as possible. As stated, this website has been created for cultural and historical purposes only — it is in no way the tool of any political ideology. This way, this historical period can be preserved for future generations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Who is this website for?</h2>
      <p>This website is for anyone who is deeply interested in history — particularly the Cold War era in the countries of the communist bloc. It is also a useful place for curious visitors who have heard of Bulgaria and would like to visit, or who want to buy a souvenir from the former People's Republic of Bulgaria.</p>
    </div>

